<title>Substitution Ciphers</title>


<section>
<title>Introduction</title>
<p>
A <em>substitution cipher</em> in its simplest form is simply a permutation of the letters in an alphabet; more complicated substitution ciphers might map single characters to fixed-size blocks of characters.
</p>
